<p>A double-decker bus drove into a bus stop in central Stockholm on Friday, killing three people and injuring three others, police and local outlets reported. The collision happened in the Östermalm district during rush hour and emergency services attended the scene; the driver was arrested at or near the site, officials said. Authorities said they have opened an investigation to establish the circumstances of the crash while the scene was secured for enquiries.</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/cqUPAgnLTw8OYILzkPkLBS3frVA85NlVPG_0Co0-peq-zMezxCNuN-NU9k0DNF7c3qLJG2KbgOuX5RgdEqGI7lhQrJSSr7gHVXB4W92aJ0OeuIs-g-eiWnDNI0dcxjHXDkZutzgW4ZCHdgG4RDaF_cfJJZ0GBvBVedl6BwYxQQ' alt='Emergency response near a bus stop after a double-decker bus crashed in Stockholm' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Victim context: Reports say the people struck were pedestrians at a bus stop rather than passengers on the vehicle, according to French reporting from the scene.</li><li>Police stance: Stockholm police told media there is currently no indication the crash was deliberate, urging caution until investigations conclude.</li><li>Legal steps: Prosecutors have launched a manslaughter-style probe to determine whether criminal charges apply as investigators examine the driver&#x27;s actions and vehicle circumstances.</li><li>Scene response: Photographs and reporting show first responders and emergency crews working at the Östermalm location while police cordoned the area for enquiries.</li></ul><blockquote>There is currently no indication that the incident was intentional - Stockholm police</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Stockholm police: There is currently no indication that the incident was intentional, officials said as they secured the scene and questioned witnesses. (<a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/c629m7jm777o'>BBC</a>)</li><li>Swedish prosecutors: Prosecutors have opened an investigation focused on possible manslaughter as they seek to determine the circumstances leading to the crash. (<a href='https://www.lemonde.fr/en/international/article/2025/11/14/three-killed-as-stockholm-bus-slams-into-pedestrians_6747467_4.html'>Le Monde</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.pbs.org/newshour/world/double-decker-bus-crashes-into-stockholm-bus-stop-killing-3-people-and-injuring-3'>Double-decker bus crashes into Stockholm bus stop, killing 3 people and injuring 3</a> - pbs.org</li><li><a href='https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/bus-crashes-bus-stop-stockholm-causes-fatalities-police-127527890'>Bus crashes into bus stop in Stockholm, killing 3 people and injuring 3</a> - abcnews.go.com</li><li><a href='https://www.dw.com/en/sweden-3-killed-after-bus-crashes-into-bus-stop/a-74753082'>Sweden: 3 killed after bus crashes into bus stop</a> - dw.com</li><li><a href='https://japantoday.com/category/world/several-people-killed-as-bus-crashes-into-stop-in-stockholm-police-say'>Several people killed as bus crashes into stop in Stockholm, police say</a> - japantoday.com</li><li><a href='https://www.lemonde.fr/en/international/article/2025/11/14/three-killed-as-stockholm-bus-slams-into-pedestrians_6747467_4.html'>Three killed as Stockholm bus slams into pedestrians</a> - lemonde.fr</li><li><a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/c629m7jm777o'>Three killed after bus crashes into Stockholm bus stop</a> - bbc.com</li><li><a href='https://www.aftonbladet.se/nyheter/a/KMEJJM/buss-korde-in-i-busskar'>At least three people are killed and three others are injured when a bus crashes into a bus stop in Östermalm, Stockholm, Sweden. (Aftonbladet in Swedish)</a> - aftonbladet.se</li></ul>